args: I thought they were never gonna give up...\nNow the sun's gone down and my legs are\nDYING for a rest.
Oh, it's just a cat. Sheesh, kitty!\nYou almost gave me a heart attack!
Hee hee. That kitty sure was cute.\nFriendly, too, which might mean\nthere's a village nearby.
Why does nighttime make everything so\nmuch scarier? If there IS a village around,\nI should head there to rest a spell.
GAH! Where's an inn when you need it?!
Phew... I've never felt so relieved to see\npeople's lights on.
But they're probably gonna be wary if a\nstranger like me waltzes into their home...
GYAAAH! I'm sorry! I'm sorry! Don't eat me;\nI'm all sinew and gristle! Someone heeelp!
Whoa, easy! I live here in this\nvillage—and we don't eat people.
I came over because I thought you might\nneed some help. I didn't think I'd make\nyou jump outta your skin like that.
I'm so sorry... I'm just, uh, easily spooked,\nand the forest's so creepy at night that it's\ngot me on edge.
Ha ha. You're not wrong there.
(Hm? This is the same acidic smell\nfrom before...)
I could set you up with a room for the \nnight if you want. You interested?
Are you sure? Oh, you're a lifesaver!
No prob.\nJust trying to be a good Samaritan.
You're really sure I can use this room?
Certainly. I've been filled in on\nyour situation—it's not much,\nbut it's a bed for the night.
If there's anything else you need, we can\nbring it to your room, so don't hesitate to\nlet us know.
Oh, thank you!\nYou're both far too kind.
Think nothing of it. But I would recommend\nyou stay in your room until dawn breaks.
A wise suggestion. The forest is\nfull of nocturnal fiends, and we\ndon't want you getting hurt.
Oh, you don't need to tell me twice.\nI'm terrified of things that go bump in\nthe night even at the best of times.
Sounds like you're all set, then.
We'll leave you in peace now.\nMay the Goddess be with you.
...I'm just imagining things, right?\nI must be. Okay, let me get some rest.

This has been quite a day. I'm going
to fall asleep the second my head hits
the pillow. But I think I'll leave the light
on, just in case.
Huh? It's awfully late for there to be\npeople talking so loudly outside.
(One of those voices sounds like the man\nwho invited me in! And did they just say\nthey have this house surrounded?!)
(What do I do?! I've gotta run!\nBut WHERE? It's pitch black outside!)
(Ugh... I hate the dark. But the thought\nof getting caught here is even scarier,\nso I have to buck up and do this!)

(Or maybe I should try and hold out here
until someone comes to help? Although,
who's to say help is coming in the first
place? Raphael, what should I dooo...?)
The window! She's trying to escape!
But we've got men outside there.\nWhat are they doing?!
Rrrrgh, AFTER HER! And tell the soldiers\nin the forest—we're gonna need their help\nin apprehending her!

*pant* *pant* I feel like I've run a
marathon today...and now I'm back in this
creepy forest! I am one hundred percent
expecting to see a ghost at this point.
But I can't cause trouble for the others.\nI need to swallow my fear and shake\nmy pursuers all on my own.
She can't have gone far. Don't leave\na corner of this forest unchecked!
Why are they so darned persistent?!\nI need to get farther away from the village!
*pant* *pant*\nSurely they won't follow me this far.\nWait... Isn't that—?
Hey there, Ryszarda.\nFigured you'd run this way.
Finally, some friendly faces!\nI'm so glad you're here to help.
Ow! That's not funny, Ramiel.\nYou've always been a joker, but\nyou're starting to scare me here.
This is no joke. Or do we need to make\nthe situation a little clearer for you?
This can't be happening...\nWe're both apostles! Friends!
We might both be apostles, but that just\nmeans we're fighting for the same thing.\nFriendship has nothing to do with it.
I'll do what I must to see a job done—\neven if that means facing a fellow apostle.
You dummy! You're always so quick to\nslack off, so why the serious act now?!
Because when you release your full\npotential, he and Basileus are the\nonly ones able to compete.
When I get told I'm the only man for the\njob, I've gotta put my back into it. Y'know?
So in the Goddess's name,\nI hereby charge you with murder.\nYou're coming with me.
